	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Sometimes your pet is going to outdamage you; you do still get experience from the kill, just not quite as much as you normally would. In fact, if your pet can outdamage you and not take too much damage, you can earn experience quite a bit faster by letting it mostly solo mobs while you conserve mana.<br><br>Going after red and yellow mobs is what is hurting you the most here. Those mobs are resisting a bit more of your damage, and they have more hitpoints due to their level, so it's taking you more nukes to take them down.<br><br>Your best bet is to find a place with some blue/even/low yellow mobs you can kill, preferably mobs with fewer hitpoints for there level than average. Lavastorm Mountains is a great example; mobs like lava basilisks and fire elementals don't have a lot of hitpoints for their level because they have magical attacks. In the case of the basilisks, you can easily avoid the stun attack since your pet will be up front taking the damage (and it seems to recover very fast from this type of spell), and in the case of elementals, you can dispell the damage shield with Cancel Magic. The result is some pretty fast experience and excellent loot for your level.<br><br>Also, you don't have to use your biggest nukes all the time. Often, you can do more damage for less mana if you stick to one or two spells from earlier levels, and keep one current spell memorized for when you need to really do some damage quickly.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
