	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=12&mid=98633049356970>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98633049356970>RE: How to outdamage your pet?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98633049356970#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Apr 3rd 4:41 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>390 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I am not really seeing how you can not outdamage your pet at your level. Unless your pet is wielding a weapon that makes it hit for 20 or more damage, then you should have no problems at your level. For example, if you are fighting wisps, then 4 or 5 nukes will be enough to outdamage your pet. If you have 156 int, then 4 or 5 nukes should only be 2 bubbles of mana. At your level 2 bubbles of mana only means 2 minutes of downtime. <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   I think your problem might be that you are trying to outdamage your pet TOO much. Do a practice fight on whatever you are fighting to see about how much HP it has. The next time you go into a fight, try to do 55-60% of the damage to your creature with your nukes. You don't need to do more than that.<br><br>Former Everquest Addict.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
